name: WSJ
text: The most important 30 minutes of this year’s presidential campaign will be the first half-hour of tonight's debate. In that crucial period, Joe Biden will have his best chance to show voters he’s up to the job, writes @GeraldFSeib. https://t.co/bh03rvK0lK

name: WSJ
text:
Trump’s unconventional political instincts will compete with Biden’s more traditional debate preparations, as the candidates meet for the first time on stage. Follow live analysis. https://t.co/p0WXi96MYY

Plus, watch #Debate2020 live at 9 p.m. ET. https://t.co/eg5hvMxXXL

name: WSJ
text: The Treasury is aiming to begin approving small-business owners’ forgiveness requests by late this week or early next, following criticism that the process for turning the loans into grants has been too slow and onerous https://t.co/k7gmXQBt0e

name: WSJ
text: With Republican leaders on a fast-paced course to confirm Judge Amy Coney Barrett to the Supreme Court by Election Day, Barrett met with Republican senators Tuesday in her first appearance on Capitol Hill since she was nominated by President Trump https://t.co/ZRHPlBwlfP

name: WSJ
text: Watch the first 2020 presidential debate between President Trump and Democratic nominee Joe Biden in Cleveland, preceded by a conversation with WSJ’s @shelbyholliday and @GeraldFSeib #Debates2020 https://t.co/b81LwVTOze

name: WSJ
text: President Trump and Joe Biden took the stage a little after 9 p.m., and did not shake hands. Moderator Chris Wallace immediately jumped into a question about the Supreme Court. #Debates2020 https://t.co/Ws7zm7FU3E https://t.co/Gb6LK3l7PT

name: WSJ
text: After a sharp exchange about health care, the topic shifted to the Covid-19 crisis with Biden accusing Trump of being ill-prepared to handle the pandemic. "It is what it is because you are who you are." #DemDebates2020 https://t.co/4C7jXYVqrb

name: WSJ
text: President Trump described why "a lot of people think that masks are not good" earlier this month. His example: Waiters. #Debates2020 #WSJTalk2020 https://t.co/ZpruNeOoEo

name: WSJ
text: As expected, President Trump went after former Vice President Joe Biden over his son Hunter’s business dealings and alleged he had earned billions from work related to China and Ukraine #Debates2020 https://t.co/zx0gxilvra

name: WSJ
text: As Joe Biden talked about his plans to repeal some of the tax cuts passed under President Trump and impose taxes on companies that pay little to the U.S. now, the president said that Biden had served for many years and didn’t take action #Debates2020 https://t.co/4e3QQfcIKF https://t.co/3MzGBIHONl

name: WSJ
text: President Trump was asked whether he was willing to condemn white supremacist and militia groups and to call for them to “stand down” and not incite violence. “I would say, almost everything I see is from the left wing.” #Debates2020 https://t.co/skxQh81MuF https://t.co/G8OR6Hny4V
